<TITLE> 7-yr-old, 5 others die in Tangail crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  Six people, including a 7-year-old girl, were killed when a passenger bus skidded off the road into a ditch after smashing into a tempo in Mirzapur, Tangail, Friday. Officer-in-charge of Mirzapur Police Station Badrul Alam told bdnews24.com the accident occurred at around 9:30am. "A Bogra-bound bus of Ekota Paribahan coming from Dhaka crushed a tempo in Kuroni. It crashed into a roadside ditch as the driver lost control over the steering," said Alam. Four persons died on the scene and two others died at Mirzapur Kumudini Hospital, he said. "After the bus was pulled out of the water at around 2pm, the body of a child was found inside." The child has been identified as a 7 year-old girl named Sumaiya. The other five deceased were passengers of the tempofour males who have been identified and a 40 year-old unidentified woman. Sumaiya, of Mongla village in Patuakhali, was travelling with her mother to her father's work place. Her father Ruhul Amin is an army man posted at Bogra Cantonment. Ten people have been admitted to Kumudini Hospital with injuries, according to police. Police seized the two vehicles but the drivers fled the scene. bdnews24.c
